l","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#ai-ops","cachedResultName":"#ai-ops"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[9369,1420],"id":"a2b70618-5484-4875-87b1-2fbc23a78745","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"operation":"append","documentId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"list","value":"","cachedResultName":"Request Tracker"},"sheetName":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"Main","cachedResultName":"Main"},"columns":{"mappingMode":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[9693,1420],"id":"afc29ae6-c1a0-4960-b10c-c3c51c7953d3","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### When Chat Message Received\n\nOpens a hosted chat session; every user message starts an execution with `chatInput` + `sessionId`.\n\nNext: Keep Valid Requests","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"9a6336b5-b887-0634-14ab-ccb35d05c92d","name":"Note: When Chat Message Received"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Keep Valid Requests\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Classify with AI","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"a5b22917-88ac-c0fd-334a-003967755287","name":"Note: Keep Valid Requests"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Classify with AI\n\nLLM classification into: Question, Complaint, Feedback (+fallback). Output port order matches this list.\n\nPorts: ①→ Store as Question · ②→ Store as Complaint, Capture Failure Context · ③→ Store as Feedback · ④→ Alert Slack — Other\n\n⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"a64e4764-b9e6-b06d-2107-e36eff0366e5","name":"Note: Classify with AI"},{"parameters":{"content":"### OpenRouter Chat Model\n\nChat model powering the AI step (model: `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5`). Swap providers here without rewiring.\n\nFeeds **Classify with AI** as `languageModel`\n\n🔑 OpenRouter API key","width":280,"height":232,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[561,1090],"id":"6c1a8d0b-9d47-f7f6-6659-e8724457ce3f","name":"Note: OpenRouter Chat Model"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Question\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[885,40],"id":"4deb1de6-9dce-b7c3-f222-f7b07ecafbe7","name":"Note: Store as Question"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Complaint\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1209,490],"id":"84adcb70-a4e0-4888-3ddc-28e828f4f1cd","name":"Note: Store as Complaint"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Store as Feedback\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1533,940],"id":"e30bb967-b86a-0a2a-af0f-29c3c2c66fec","name":"Note: Store as Feedback"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Alert Slack — Other\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Reunite Branches · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1857,1390],"id":"b4f38819-c05d-5fa2-2259-326f52ac78ed","name":"Note: Alert Slack — Other"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reunite Branches\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2505,520],"id":"4086403d-5069-689f-1420-5f244677ca86","name":"Note: Reunite Branches"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nnotion — `getAll` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3477,520],"id":"7c4a509e-16f9-50d4-8cf6-6e50d4b068b1","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3801,520],"id":"c8aeb5c2-068d-814c-9bb2-cd5105c4ce25","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4125,520],"id":"af86b10a-906c-b690-fb1f-6f913605967f","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4449,520],"id":"96ccc1de-284f-bb4f-2b93-7fd57d2a5a5b","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4773,520],"id":"9fc976b1-f393-8a7a-60ed-b3d533a93086","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5097,520],"id":"3ac3f204-f8a3-64ee-d133-cce1622d4935","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5421,520],"id":"c52c4b51-90d4-e076-392e-448e621ee3e9","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fingerprint for Idempotency · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5745,520],"id":"4983945c-2b34-5494-c5b8-0d65875a2b16","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per request (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6069,520],"id":"9daf3792-bb5a-0ac5-1efc-de722b906057","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Stamp Completion Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6393,520],"id":"dedc8ed3-6a8e-4ac5-b333-70a3136ca5ad","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6717,520],"id":"aa8ed57c-85c2-094f-ac0c-955ee1ac2fa2","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Stamp Processing Time","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7041,520],"id":"07692da5-6358-bdf1-63ea-c4b927be6c4f","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Processing Time\n\nStamps `processedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty query","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7365,520],"id":"8833a71d-e65c-16c4-54c3-0c6106871fba","name":"Note: Stamp Processing Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty query\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Align Field Names","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7689,520],"id":"b4a59005-4fcb-385c-51bc-ea8d6ec3f518","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty query"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Align Field Names\n\nNormalizes field names so every source feeds the same downstream schema.\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8013,520],"id":"9925c7b2-f1d0-f7be-242a-9fd6af867846","name":"Note: Align Field Names"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Sort Requests Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8337,520],"id":"2f2ede83-a46e-5f77-c654-efc098c940a5","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Requests Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8661,520],"id":"8553a811-6280-44f4-663a-f5a81f0a6425","name":"Note: Sort Requests Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8985,520],"id":"bdb7e863-6ada-d93b-b263-0f3926c39aa1","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nnotion — `create` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9309,520],"id":"05b2ff00-d36b-3cd9-054d-ea84a8a93cd7","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9633,520],"id":"ada76cc7-ee5d-8963-bc71-eeb1e394166f","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8985,1540],"id":"9bbb0f00-1dd2-2263-4194-1a9cb144e56b","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9309,1540],"id":"ea98e9d6-5426-3089-e3b7-4ad341de6279","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9633,1540],"id":"b3bfd043-8bce-428c-1fa0-26c25897ceaa","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Reply to chat messages hands-free\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nReply to chat messages hands-free. It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual research assistant is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Keep Valid Requests → Classify with AI → Store as Question → Reunite Branches → Load Previous Snapshot → Compute Drift vs Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating research assistant in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Improves response time\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Notion integration token; OpenRouter API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"2cdb429f-3dfc-85a0-1979-35924129ffaf","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-500],"id":"697cf553-6098-f7ed-2aa3-0e934974def1","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.","width":360,"height":260,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-500],"id":"de231169-6e46-5c1f-280f-86948edbe5d5","name":"🤖 AI cluster"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-500],"id":"6b0cd6e7-87b6-dc88-4c2e-77fe07451ed4","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your research assistant process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-500],"id":"6cf43c67-586f-09d8-48ad-f568b1d90928","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"When Chat Message Received":{"main":[[{"node":"Keep Valid Requests","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Keep Valid Requests":{"main":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"main","index":0}]]},"OpenRouter Chat Model":{"ai_languageModel":[[{"node":"Classify with AI","type":"ai_languageModel","index":0}]]},"Classify with AI":{"main":[[{"node":"Store as Question","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Complaint","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Store as Feedback","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Alert Slack — Other","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Question":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Complaint":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Store as Feedback":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Alert Slack — Other":{"main":[[{"node":"Reunite Branches","type":"main","index":3}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Reunite Branches":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Processing Time","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Processing Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty query","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty query":{"main":[[{"node":"Align Field Names","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Align Field Names":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Requests Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Requests Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"be94e740-80a5-4080-9771-6d680ecf4342","id":"FDX00473"}